Has it been overdone?[/dfd_heading][vc_column_text]The presentation will cover the results of the enormous fiscal stimulus already provided (and contemplated) by the U.S. Government, and the presumed economic outlook. Likewise, it will peruse the extent and effects of the ballooning amount of monetary stimulus being provided by the Central Banks around the globe. Taking into account the staggering geopolitical factors shaping economies and markets, the outlook for stock and bond markets will be discussed.[/vc_column_text][dfd_spacer screen_wide_spacer_size="40" screen_normal_resolution="1024" screen_tablet_resolution="800" screen_mobile_resolution="480" screen_normal_spacer_size="30" screen_tablet_spacer_size="20" screen_mobile_spacer_size="15"][vc_column_text]
You will learn...

He joined Fidelity Investments in 1966. From 1972-1990, he managed the Fidelity Equity-Income Fund. During that period, the fund achieved a return of over 1100%, nearly twice that of the S&P 500 index. This return ranked him as the #1 equity-income fund manager in the nation for the 19-year period. In 1987, he was named America’s Best Income Investor by Money Magazine. Eric Kobren, former publisher of Fidelity Insight, has said Johnstone ranks “a close second” to Peter Lynch as Fidelity’s best all-time fund manager.[/vc_column_text][dfd_spacer Post-Pandemic World[/dfd_heading][vc_column_text]How has the pandemic permanently changed the U.S. economy and the rest of the world, once it is finally defeated? Will the future of inflation be of a transitory nature or permanently higher going forward? How high will inflation be, and what will be the impact on interest rates? Given these new and emerging macro-economic trends what sectors and industry groups will thrive and which will do poorly in the new post-pandemic world? Don't miss Jason Trennert's presentation as he explores these questions and more, in order to help investors navigate the current macro environment.[/vc_column_text][dfd_spacer screen_wide_spacer_size="40" screen_normal_resolution="1024" screen_tablet_resolution="800" screen_mobile_resolution="480" screen_normal_spacer_size="30" screen_tablet_spacer_size="20" screen_mobile_spacer_size="15"][vc_column_text]

In 2006, Trennert co-founded Strategas. Prior to founding Strategas, he was the chief investment strategist and a senior managing director at International Strategy & Investment (ISI) Group. He is a regular guest on business news programs broadcast by CNBC, CNBC Italia, Fox Business News and Bloomberg TV, among others. Trennert has an MBA from The Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania and B.S. in international economics from Georgetown University.[/vc_column_text][dfd_spacer screen_wide_spacer_size="20" screen_normal_resolution="1024" screen_tablet_resolution="800" screen_mobile_resolution="480" screen_normal_spacer_size="15" screen_tablet_spacer_size="15" screen_mobile_spacer_size="10"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_separator color="blue"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/6"][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][dfd_spacer screen_wide_spacer_size="40" screen_normal_resolution="1024" screen_tablet_resolution="800" screen_mobile_resolution="480" screen_normal_spacer_size="30" screen_tablet_spacer_size="20" screen_mobile_spacer_size="15"][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][dfd_spacer screen_wide_spacer_size="40" screen_normal_resolution="1024" screen_tablet_resolution="800" screen_mobile_resolution="480" screen_normal_spacer_size="30" screen_tablet_spacer_size="20" screen_mobile_spacer_size="15"][vc_column_text]
